{
  "texts": [
    "There is much literature on DL-based image synthesis.",
    "Future studies need to address specific unanswered questions.",
    "Since GPU memory constraints prevented training on three-dimensional (3D) slices, some DL algorithms were trained on two-dimensional (2D) slices.",
    "Unlike 3D loss functions, 2D loss functions do not consider continuity in the third dimension, thus making slices appear discontinuous.",
    "In addition to using 3D patches to train models that exploit 3D spatial information more effectively, they can also extract features from larger-scale images (34, 81)."
  ]
}